INT; sparse: # Parts-per-thousand of total biome area in BiomeData.homeworld_area.
# Positive integers indicate national territory; negative numbers indicate resource exploitation outside of national territory (oceans in particular)
# Use "earth other" to sum to 1000 so earth biomes are accurately summed.
# Almost all values here are guesses, except: Total ag area (from data.worldbank.org) divided by world biome "cropland" area; Urban & dense-settlement are based on current share of world population.
